gurmukhi: AnKyd Byd ACyd ] muKcwr gwvq byd ]4]34]
transliteration: Ankhed Bhed Achhed|| Moukhchaar Gadvat Bed||4||34||
translation: He is Indestructible with Imperishable mysteries, and the four-handed Brahma sings the Vedas. 4.34.

gurmukhi: ijh nyq ingm khMq ] suKcwr bkq ibAMq ]
transliteration: Jih Net Nigad Kahant|| Moukhchaar Bakat Biant||
translation: To Him, the Nigam (Vedas) call “Neti” (Not this). The four-handed Brahma Speak of Him as Unlimited.

gurmukhi: AniB`j Aqul pRqwp ] AnKMf Aimq Aqwp ]5]35]
translation: His Glory is Unaffected and Inestimable, He is Undivided, Unlimited and Un-established. 5.35.

gurmukhi: ijh kIn jgq pswr ] ricE ibcwr ibcwr ]
transliteration: Jih Koon Jagad Pasaar|| Rachio Bichaar Bichaar||
translation: He, who hath created the expanse of the world, He hath Created it in full Consciousness.

gurmukhi: AnMq rUp AKMf ] Aqul pRqwp pRcMf ]6]36]
transliteration: Anant Roop Akhannd|| Atul Prataap Prachanndd||6||36||
translation: His Infinite Form is Indivisible, His Immeasurable Glory is Powerful 6.36.

gurmukhi: ijh AMf qy bHsMf ] kIny su cOdh KMf ]
transliteration: Jih And Te Brahmand|| Koone Su Chaudah Khand||
translation: He, who hath Created the universe from the Cosmic egg, He hath Created the fourteen regions.

gurmukhi: sB kIn jgq pswr ] AibXkq rUp audwr ]7]37]
transliteration: Sabh Koon Jagad Pasaar|| Abiyakat Roop Udaar||7||37||
translation: He hath Created all the expanse of the world. That Benevolent Lord is Unmanifested. 7.37.

gurmukhi: ijh koit ieMdR niRpwr ] keI bHm ibsn ibcwr ]
transliteration: Jih Kottee Indra Nripaar|| Kaee Brahm Bisan Bichaar||
translation: He, who hath Created millions of king Indras, He hath Created many Brahmas and Vishnus after consideration.

gurmukhi: keI rwm kiRsn rsUl ] ibnu Bgq ko n kbUl ]8]38]
transliteration: Kaee Raam Krisan Rasool|| Bin(u) Bhagad Ko Na Kabool||8||38||
translation: He hath Created many Ramas, Krishnas and Rasuls (Prophets), none of them is approved by the Lord without devotion. 8.38.

gurmukhi: keI isMD ibMD nigMdR ] keI m`C k`C PinMdR ]
transliteration: Kaee Sindh Bindh Nagindra|| Kaee Machchh Kachchh Phanindra||
translation: Created many oceans and mountains like Vindhyachal; many fish incarnations, tortoise incarnations and Sheshanagas.

gurmukhi: keI dyv Awid kumwr ] keI kiRsn ibsn Avqwr ]9]39]
transliteration: Kaee Dev Aadh Koumaar|| Kaee Krisan Bisan Avtaar||9||39||
translation: Created many gods, and Adi Kumars, sons of Brahma (Sanak, Sanandan, Sanatan and Sant Kumar), many Krishnas and incarnations of Vishnu.9.39.

gurmukhi: keI ieMdR bwr buhwr ] keI byd Aau muKcwr ]
transliteration: Kaee Indra Baar Buhaar|| Kaee Bed Au Moukhchaar||
translation: Many Indras sweep at His door. Many Vedas and four-headed Brahmas are there.

gurmukhi: keI rudR C`dR srUp ] keI rwm kiRsn AnUp ]10]40]
transliteration: Kaee Rudra Chhudra Daroop|| Kaee Raam Krisan Anoop||10||40||
translation: Many Rudras (Shivas) of ghastly appearance are there; many unique Ramas and Krishnas are there. 10.40.

gurmukhi: keI kok kwb BxMq ] keI byd Byd khMq ]
transliteration: Kaee Kok Kaab Bhanant|| Kaee Bed Bhed Kahant||
translation: Many poets compose poetry there; many speak of the distinction of the knowledge of Vedas.
